{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs-tree-items): 17 structured seeds across all six parsers\n\nfuzz_btrfs_tree_items pipes the same bytes through six parsers in\nparallel \u2014 parse_root_item / parse_root_ref / parse_inode_item /\nparse_dir_items / parse_xattr_items / parse_extent_data \u2014 and asserts\nfield-level invariants on every successful decode. The previous corpus\nof 3 ad-hoc seeds (seed_root_item, seed_dir_items, seed_extent_data)\nexercised only one happy path per parser at most, and only with\ndefault field values. libFuzzer would eventually find the rest, but\nseeded shapes drive the success branches at run-1.\n\nAdds 17 seeds, each crafted to drive ONE specific parser onto its\nhappy path (and incidentally walk the early-error code in the other\nfive):\n\n  * parse_root_item: legacy 239-byte minimal, max-level (level=7)\n    boundary, fully-extended 279-byte form with matching\n    generation_v2 + uuid + parent_uuid, and the BTRFS_ROOT_SUBVOL_RDONLY\n    flag bit.\n  * parse_root_ref: short ASCII name; long realistic subvolume name.\n  * parse_inode_item: zero-mtime defaults; realistic uid/gid/mode\n    plus three independent timestamp fields.\n  * parse_dir_items: single 30-byte header + name; three concatenated\n    items that exercise the inter-item boundary walk.\n  * parse_xattr_items: a single user.tag entry; two back-to-back\n    entries spanning user.* and security.* namespaces.\n  * parse_extent_data: inline body, regular extent (type=1), prealloc\n    extent (type=2), Zstd-compressed regular extent (compression=3).\n  * universal short input (12 bytes) that fires every parser's\n    InsufficientData branch in one run.\n\nValidated by a 16 s libFuzzer run: 2.25 M executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
